 /usr/share/applications will list out all .desktop applications installed on your computer. These files are sort like Windows start menu shorcuts, they are not applications.

type which application-name in terminal will show you where the executable of the application is located.  
 
type whereis application-name in terminal will show you where are all the files of the application are located. 

The programs on Linux are actually not located on any single place, instead the program's files are distributed around the filesystem, depends on its purpose.
For example the executables are in /usr/bin, icons in /usr/share/icons, libraries in /usr/share/pixmpas and so on.
The rest of the files with no specific place are stored in /usr/share/application-name



